  "texts": [
    "As previewed in § 1, in § 2.5, § 5.2, and § 7.1 we will show that full possibility frames provide a more general semantics for normal modal logics than Kripke frames; and in § 5.5, we will show that general possibility frames provide a fully general semantics.Two of our three examples of partial-state frames from § 2.1 are examples of possibility frames.",
    "Example 2.22 (World Frames Cont.).",
    "One can check that every world frame, viewed as a partial-state frame as in Example 2.6, is a possibility frame, and every full world frame is a full possibility frame.",
